<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-30T17:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-30T17:40:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1122.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-30T18:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Revolution breaking out at La Vega, Santiago. If we strengthen the
                            Provisional Government’s arms with funds the outbreak can be suppressed
                            in its inception. Important that Arias should not be permitted to get a
                            start.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>